								<div class="title" id="post-title-2474996">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/nighkos" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1658000); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1658000&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610164273" alt="Nighkos" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1658000)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/nighkos" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1658000); return false;" >Nighkos</a></span> <span class="odate time_1458307046 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">18 Mar 2016 13:17</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2474996">
									

<p>Hey guys. I haven't been active on the site, as I've been real busy with other things. However, I try to keep an eye on it every once in a while, and a message from Voct let me know about this. So, I'll go ahead and give my thoughts.</p>
<p>Short Answer:<br />
3rd description is Chaos Insurgency, 4th is Prometheus Labs, 5th is UIU.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Long&nbsp;Answer</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;OK,&nbsp;geez&nbsp;sorry&nbsp;I&nbsp;asked</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>My goal with these Aliases was to spark peoples' imagination with who knows about the object and what they want with it. I also wanted to make formats that felt genuine for each group.</p>
<p>Since in most incarnations, the Chaos Insurgency is all about using anomalies, I wanted a &quot;SCP&quot; type number that reflected the items usefulness. The &quot;AA&quot; is a broad classification of the item's abilities. The &quot;.2&quot; is a more specific grouping within the &quot;AA&quot; group and relates to how the abilities are used. The &quot;143&quot; is the actual ID number of the item. Finally, the &quot;(85/10)&quot; is a shorthand for comparing the Potential Benefit of using the object vs the Threat or Danger of of using the object.</p>
<p>With Prometheus Labs, I wanted to imply their desire to replicate the object's abilities. Naming the project &quot;Orpheus&quot; is a pretty straightforward reference to what they wanted to do.</p>
<p>The final one is UIU. With this, a complex, unintelligible serial number seems perfect for a government agency. UI is the &quot;casefile&quot; or cereal number for the incident, whereas &quot;OBJ&quot; signifies that the case is related to an item (rather than event). With this inclusion, I wanted to imply that this item and it's abilities were not as secret as the Foundation might like.</p>
<p>But, despite everything that I've said, I kept it vague for a reason. My goal here was to spark the reader's imagination, so I don't want my intent to be the &quot;cannon&quot; interpretation. If you think it would be more interesting to think of these Aliases in terms of other groups, like ORIA or MC&amp;D, by all means, feel free to!</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

